In [[Norse mythology]], '''Ægir''' (also Aegir) ([[Old Norse]] "sea")<ref name=LINDOW47>Lindow (2001:47).</ref> is a sea [[jötunn]] associated with the [[ocean]]. He is also known for being a friend of the [[Æsir|gods]] and hosting elaborate parties for them.

He is the namesake for the exoplanet previously known as [[Epsilon Eridani b]].

Ægir's servants are [[Fimafeng]] (killed by [[Loki]]) and [[Eldir]].

